com.maxleap

Class MaxLeap

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.maxleap.MaxLeap

  • public class MaxLeap
extends Object
    The MaxLeap class contains static functions that handle global configuration for the MaxLeap library.

    • Method Detail

      • initialize

        public static void initialize(Context context)
        Authenticates this client as belonging to your application.

        You must define com.maxleap.APPLICATION_ID and com.maxleap.CLIENT_KEY meta-data in your AndroidManifest.xml: 

         <manifest ...>

 ...

   <application ...>
     <meta-data
       android:name="com.maxleap.APPLICATION_ID"
       android:value="@string/ml_app_id" />
     <meta-data
       android:name="com.maxleap.CLIENT_KEY"
       android:value="@string/ml_client_key" />

       ...

   </application>
 </manifest>

        Parameters:
        context - the application context
